OL,3,CRAF veteran Derrick Grubb celebrates
OL,4,C100 years of his 'good life'
OL,6,FMr Grubb joined the RAF in July 1942
OL,7,Fand served with the 112 Squadron, one
OL,8,Fof the first squadrons to receive the
OL,9,FCurtiss P40 Kittyhawk fighter bomber.
OL,11,FWhile based in Italy in 1943, he was
OL,12,Fshot down and captured as a prisoner
OL,13,Fof war and held for a year before he
OL,14,Fwas forced to march hundreds of miles
OL,15,Fwestwards as the German army retreated
OL,16,Fat the end of the war.
OL,18,FMr Grubb, who served in the RAF for 34
OL,19,Fyears, went on to write a book about
OL,20,Fhis experiences and to educate his
OL,21,Fgrandchildren.
