OL,3,CRAF veteran Derrick Grubb celebrates
OL,4,C100 years of his 'good life'
OL,6,FExplaining why it was still important
OL,7,Fto commemorate the war, he added:
OL,8,F"It's a sad time but it's something to
OL,9,Fbe remembered and I am sure we will
OL,10,Falways remember it because it's a damn
OL,11,Fgood job it was finished.
OL,13,F"At the time, as a young man of 18
OL,14,Fwhen I joined up, everything was so
OL,15,Fnew, I hadn't been out of the country
OL,16,Fbefore, going to South Africa, on a
OL,17,Ftrain for two days going up to
OL,18,FRhodesia, Zimbabwe now, trained as a
OL,19,Fpilot there then went up to the Middle
OL,20,FEast and Italy and then I got shot
OL,21,Fdown.
