OL,3,CRAF veteran Derrick Grubb celebrates
OL,4,C100 years of his 'good life'
OL,6,F"It was an adventure for an 18-year-
OL,7,Fold boy at the time and that's how you
OL,8,Flooked upon it and the same with the
OL,9,FPOW camp and the long march but it is
OL,10,Fwhen you get to this age and you think
OL,11,Fabout it, it was all terrible, it
OL,12,Fshouldn't have been there, it had to
OL,13,Fbe done.
OL,15,F"I was happy I was there. If I had the
OL,16,Fchance again, I would go only because
OL,17,Fit affected us so much and if they had
OL,18,Foverrun us like they did the other
OL,19,Fcountries and treated us like the
OL,20,Fothers ... it should never be done
OL,21,Fagain."
